name: Bash-Script-CVE-2018-16763
description: FUEL CMS 1.4.1 allows PHP Code Evaluation via the pages/select/ filter parameter or the preview/ data parameter. This can lead to Pre-Auth Remote Code Execution.

name: Bash-Script-CVE-2019-17662
description: ThinVNC 1.0b1 is vulnerable to arbitrary file read, which leads to a compromise of the VNC server. The vulnerability exists even when authentication is turned on during the deployment of the VNC server. The password for authentication is stored in cleartext in a file that can be read via a ../../ThinVnc.ini directory traversal attack vector.

name: OMIGOD_cve-2021-38647
description: CVE-2021-38647 is an unauthenticated RCE vulnerability effecting the OMI agent as root.

name: cpe2cve
description: Compute public vulnerabilities from a list of product in the CPE format
